<br>
As you go up in lvls, your aggro radius slowly gets smaller.  It's not really noticable until post 50.<br>
<br>
What I mean by aggro radius is both the distance at which mobs will aggro on you, and also the distance at which mobs will assist-aggro on you.<br>
<br>
Example: lvl 45 pulling in Karnor's.  Their aggro radius is huge so when they pull they will usually get several adds.  A lvl 55 doesn't have this problem because mobs have to be much closer in order to assist-aggro on the puller.<br>
<br>
Remember that spells have varying effects on aggro radii.  ie DDs tend to aggro much farther out than dispells do. <p><IMG SRC="http://lordfate.homestead.com/files/misc/sig.jpg"></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ukhardan.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Khardan</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_fire.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(4/12/01 5:57:45 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovespells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2320.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.csun.edu/~hbcsc544/burnsig.jpg width=144 height=159></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Using invis vs animal to kite ?</span><hr size=1> I've used camo to pull mobs thru differing/un factioned, yet still KoS to me mobs. . .works wonderfully. . .tho im sure if i pulled Priest Ganek past Priest Bjorn while invis Bjorn would aggro (both level 55 mobs on same faction) haven't had the chance to try it. <p><p><center><br>
